22/10/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Speaking during a roundtable discussion at the National Institute of Justice on Friday (October 20th), US Ambassador to Sofia John Beyrle praised the work of Bulgarian Chief Prosecutor Boris Velchev.
According to Beyrle, there has been an evident change in the Bulgarian prosecution's activities since Velchev's appointment earlier this year, and previously noticed setbacks are being overcome.
(Sega, Monitor - 21/10/06)
